Mike is a graphic designer by day and an illustrator by night. He enjoys drawing baseball players, rock stars, and real people. When not drawing, you can catch Mike listening to rock and roll music, eating potato-based foods, or walking around Philadelphia, where he lives.

Philly-enthusiast, athlete, painter and world-traveler.  Britt Miller has been actively painting and selling works since 2004.  After completing her undergraduate program, Britt launched an online art space and began participating in local exhibitions and shows.  She graduated from Temple University's International MBA program while living in France, India, China, and Japan.  She has completed several triathlons and seven marathons.

Visual artist, designer by trade, artist by nature, painter by passion, collaborator by desire, and creative by DNA.  Sean Martorana is a 2001 graphic design graduate from The Art Institute of Philadelphia. Upon graduation, Sean was hired at a print shop where he helped customers with small design jobs and expanded the services to include full-fledged brand development and marketing. He branched off and founded the visual design, marketing, and communications firm THE_STUDiO.  Check out more of Sean's artwork at seanmartorana.com.
